    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2008 Corvette Z06 is a visceral example of American engineering, powered by the naturally aspirated 7.0L LS7 V8 featuring titanium intake valves and connecting rods. The hydroformed aluminum chassis and magnesium roof structure provide a high strength-to-weight ratio, ensuring exceptional torsional rigidity. Power is delivered through a rear-mounted Tremec TR-6060 six-speed manual transaxle and a limited-slip differential with a 3.42 final drive ratio. The dry-sump oiling system and oil-to-air coolers ensure thermal stability during high-load cycles. While the exterior displays minor road-derived patina, the mechanical components\u2014including the transverse leaf spring suspension and massive six-piston front monoblock calipers\u2014remain in excellent working order, offering a raw, analog driving experience that modern grand tourers cannot replicate.",
